No!

306
00:37:39,820 --> 00:37:41,140
(GUN FIRES)

307
00:37:42,780 --> 00:37:44,500
(GUN FIRES)

308
00:37:50,780 --> 00:37:52,340
(DOG BARKS)

309
00:40:01,380 --> 00:40:06,220
SULLIVAN:
No! My God!

310
00:40:42,300 --> 00:40:45,450
- Pa, I'm sorry.
- Stupid!

311
00:40:45,740 --> 00:40:48,970
The kid would've talked. I'm sorry.

312
00:40:49,460 --> 00:40:53,460
Goddamn you. Goddamn you!

313
00:40:53,740 --> 00:40:59,820
I curse the fucking day you were born!

314
00:41:00,300 --> 00:41:02,690
I curse it!

315
00:41:05,260 --> 00:41:06,540
You!

316
00:41:12,940 --> 00:41:15,010
Oh, Lord.

317
00:41:18,260 --> 00:41:22,860
Oh, Lord. God help us.

318
00:41:23,100 --> 00:41:24,980
God help us.

319
00:41:36,380 --> 00:41:40,010
This house is not our home anymore.

320
00:41:40,340 --> 00:41:42,900
It's just an empty building.

321
00:42:08,580 --> 00:42:11,460
All right, you stay here.
You stay out of sight.

322
00:42:11,620 --> 00:42:13,610
- Don't go, Pa. Don't go.
- Michael...

323
00:42:14,060 --> 00:42:17,290
...when they find out we're gone,
they're gonna come after us.

324
00:42:17,460 --> 00:42:19,740
I have to protect you now.

325
00:42:20,380 --> 00:42:22,580
Please, Pa.

326
00:42:26,220 --> 00:42:29,340
All right, here, take this.

327
00:42:29,540 --> 00:42:31,820
- No. I don't want it.
- Take it.

328
00:42:32,060 --> 00:42:37,140
- I don't want it.
- Boy, take it! You got six shots.

329
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:41,660
If I'm not back in half an hour, go tell
Reverend Lynch what's happened.

330
00:42:41,820 --> 00:42:44,780
Do not go to Father Callaway.

331
00:43:13,900 --> 00:43:16,130
I don't have any business with you,
Mr. Kelly.

332
00:43:16,300 --> 00:43:19,770
But I have business with you, Mike.

333
00:43:19,980 --> 00:43:22,450
Go ahead.

334
00:43:24,460 --> 00:43:26,130
What is that?

335
00:43:26,380 --> 00:43:31,060
25,000 dollars. Mr. Rooney wants you
to know there's more if you need it.

336
00:43:31,300 --> 00:43:36,170
You have friends in Ireland, Mike.
Why don't you take Peter and leave?

337
00:43:36,420 --> 00:43:39,020
I can't take Peter.

338
00:43:39,220 --> 00:43:43,500
He's dead.

339
00:43:43,660 --> 00:43:47,620
- So where's Connor?
- He's in hiding.

340
00:43:48,220 --> 00:43:50,900
- Where?
- You know I can't tell you that.

341
00:43:52,540 --> 00:43:56,420
You think sticking a gun to my head
is gonna make any difference to me?

342
00:43:56,620 --> 00:44:02,220
If I tell you, I'm a dead man anyway.
We both are.

343
00:44:02,380 --> 00:44:08,620
Think, Mike. Don't be stupid.
I'm just the messenger.

344
00:44:18,060 --> 00:44:21,580
Then give Mr. Rooney a message for me.

345
00:44:21,740 --> 00:44:23,410
What is it?

346
00:44:37,900 --> 00:44:39,650
Give me the gun.

347
00:44:51,740 --> 00:44:54,050
MICHAEL:
Where are we going?

348
00:44:54,220 --> 00:44:55,940
SULLIVAN:
To Chicago.

349
00:44:56,420 --> 00:44:58,890
There's a man there who runs things.

350
00:44:59,740 --> 00:45:01,940
I've done some work for him.

351
00:45:02,620 --> 00:45:05,340
We have to find out where he stands.

352
00:45:07,940 --> 00:45:10,140
Try to get some sleep.

353
00:46:44,340 --> 00:46:46,380
I want you to wait for me here.

354
00:46:46,620 --> 00:46:49,530
- Sure.
- I won't be long. You'll be all right?

355
00:46:49,780 --> 00:46:53,490
- Yeah, I'll be all right.
- That's a good boy.

356
00:47:39,620 --> 00:47:42,610
GUARD: Hello, Mike.
- Hello, fellas.

357
00:47:42,780 --> 00:47:48,650
It's nice to see you. We heard what
happened. How you holding up?

358
00:47:48,860 --> 00:47:51,090
I need to talk to Mr. Nitti.

359
00:47:51,980 --> 00:47:55,660
- He's awful busy.
- I can wait.

360
00:47:56,540 --> 00:47:59,500
Okay. Take the man to the top.

361
00:47:59,660 --> 00:48:01,020
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

362
00:48:54,460 --> 00:48:56,290
Certainly, sir.

363
00:49:03,340 --> 00:49:06,780
Sorry to make you wait so long, Mike.
Come on in.

364
00:49:06,940 --> 00:49:10,250
We all just heard what happened.

365
00:49:10,420 --> 00:49:13,300
Jesus, I'm sorry, Mike.

366
00:49:13,460 --> 00:49:18,700
Well, thank you for seeing me,
Mr. Nitti.

367
00:49:18,860 --> 00:49:20,450
Come on, sit down.

368
00:49:20,740 --> 00:49:22,060
- Like some coffee or...?
- No.

369
00:49:22,220 --> 00:49:24,690
- You sure?
- Yes, thank you.

370
00:49:26,300 --> 00:49:32,460
So, what can I do for you, Mike?

371
00:49:32,700 --> 00:49:34,820
I'd like to work for you.

372
00:49:38,260 --> 00:49:41,890
Well, that's very interesting.

373
00:49:42,180 --> 00:49:47,650
And in return, I'd like you to turn a
blind eye to what I have to do.

374
00:49:47,980 --> 00:49:49,500
And what is that?

375
00:49:52,420 --> 00:49:54,810
Kill the man who murdered my family.

376
00:49:55,660 --> 00:49:57,940
Is one more body
gonna make a difference?

377
00:49:59,300 --> 00:50:01,900
This is a good proposal, Mr. Nitti.

378
00:50:02,100 --> 00:50:05,730
I will work only for you,
and you know I can do a good job.

379
00:50:07,860 --> 00:50:10,220
I respect you, Mike. I do.

380
00:50:10,540 --> 00:50:15,490
We would like nothing more than to have
you come work for us. But not like this.

381
00:50:15,660 --> 00:50:18,540
What you're asking me is impossible.

382
00:50:18,820 --> 00:50:20,260
Is it?

383
00:50:22,420 --> 00:50:27,500
Let me explain something to you that
maybe you haven't realized.

384
00:50:28,620 --> 00:50:32,220
All these years, you've been living
under the protection...

385
00:50:32,380 --> 00:50:34,530
...of people who care about you.

386
00:50:34,700 --> 00:50:40,810
And those same people
are protecting you now, including me.

387
00:50:41,060 --> 00:50:45,820
So if you go ahead with this,
if you open that door...

388
00:50:45,980 --> 00:50:48,050
...you're walking through it alone.

389
00:50:48,780 --> 00:50:54,970
And all that Ioyalty, all that trust,
will no longer exist for you.

390
00:50:57,100 --> 00:51:02,970
And Mike, you won't make it.
Not on your own.

391
00:51:04,140 --> 00:51:06,740
And not with a little boy.

392
00:51:10,860 --> 00:51:13,330
You're protecting him already?

393
00:51:15,780 --> 00:51:18,250
We're protecting our interests, Mike.

394
00:51:20,340 --> 00:51:22,860
I drove all through the night
to see you.

395
00:51:23,660 --> 00:51:28,580
I appreciate that.
Now I suggest you drive yourself back.

396
00:51:34,020 --> 00:51:38,410
Go home, Mike.
Go home and bury your wife and child.

397
00:51:38,580 --> 00:51:40,460
With our blessing.

398
00:51:43,700 --> 00:51:46,010
It won't be that simple.

399
00:51:57,580 --> 00:51:59,410
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

400
00:52:21,980 --> 00:52:24,700
- You heard?
ROONEY: Mm-hm.

401
00:52:24,860 --> 00:52:28,780
Dad, listen to me.
He's in the building.

402
00:52:28,940 --> 00:52:34,540
- You can end this now. Take him now.
- Connor, get upstairs.

403
00:52:36,580 --> 00:52:38,540
All right.

404
00:52:43,220 --> 00:52:46,210
God help me.

405
00:52:46,380 --> 00:52:51,140
God help me. What do I do?

406
00:52:51,340 --> 00:52:54,970
NITTl:
You think objectively.

407
00:52:55,140 --> 00:52:57,290
And you make your choice.

408
00:52:59,700 --> 00:53:03,490
What would you do if Sullivan
were just some guy?

409
00:53:06,300 --> 00:53:10,010
God help me.

410
00:53:10,180 --> 00:53:12,540
- Make it quick.
- And the kid?

411
00:53:13,780 --> 00:53:16,460
Oh, Christ. No, no.

412
00:53:17,460 --> 00:53:22,140
One day the kid becomes a man...
Think he won't remember?

413
00:53:23,500 --> 00:53:26,060
I said not the kid.

414
00:53:27,020 --> 00:53:29,380
All right.

415
00:53:29,540 --> 00:53:31,210
I know who to call.

416
00:53:32,660 --> 00:53:36,700
There's a guy who's done some work
for us in the past.

417
00:53:36,860 --> 00:53:38,580
He's gifted.

418
00:53:50,700 --> 00:53:54,490
Excuse me, ma'am. Press. Press.

419
00:53:54,700 --> 00:53:57,090
He was raping my wife.
He raped my wife.

420
00:53:57,260 --> 00:54:00,620
OFFICER: Come on, come on,
you're treading on the evidence here.

421
00:54:07,820 --> 00:54:11,050
Two minutes.

422
00:54:11,220 --> 00:54:13,340
You got it, Mr. Maguire.

423
00:54:33,820 --> 00:54:35,970
(COUGHING)

424
00:54:58,100 --> 00:55:01,300
(TRAIN RUMBLES)

425
00:55:17,780 --> 00:55:20,420
(PHONE RINGS)

426
00:55:33,980 --> 00:55:37,530
MAGUIRE: Harlen Maguire.
Good evening, Mr. Nitti.

427
00:55:39,460 --> 00:55:40,500
Uh-huh.

428
00:55:41,140 --> 00:55:43,420
Sixteen hundred.

429
00:55:44,180 --> 00:55:46,620
Sixteen hundred dollars is my rate,
Mr. Nitti.

430
00:55:46,860 --> 00:55:49,740
And what I make on
the photographs is mine.

431
00:55:51,300 --> 00:55:52,530
Mm.

432
00:55:52,700 --> 00:55:54,220
No, never met him.

433
00:55:54,380 --> 00:55:55,700
But I know his work.

434
00:56:02,060 --> 00:56:04,340
He traveling alone?

435
00:56:06,620 --> 00:56:08,370
How old?

436
00:56:13,700 --> 00:56:15,900
What do I do with the kid?

437
00:56:17,420 --> 00:56:19,170
Mm-hm.

438
00:56:20,220 --> 00:56:21,970
Uh-huh.

439
00:56:22,820 --> 00:56:24,540
Will do.

440
00:56:25,660 --> 00:56:27,460
Thank you.

441
00:56:33,540 --> 00:56:38,010
You remember your aunt Sarah?
Your mom's sister?

442
00:56:40,060 --> 00:56:43,900
She lives in Perdition.
She'll take you in.

443
00:56:45,860 --> 00:56:47,660
Where is it?

444
00:56:47,900 --> 00:56:50,020
Right by the lake.

445
00:56:51,460 --> 00:56:56,010
We went there once, all of us,
when you were 4, maybe 5.

446
00:56:58,020 --> 00:56:59,820
It's beautiful.

447
00:57:01,140 --> 00:57:03,100
You remember?

448
00:57:06,460 --> 00:57:08,690
The place with the dog.

449
00:57:12,700 --> 00:57:15,420
(PRAYING IN LATIN)

450
00:58:57,380 --> 00:58:58,970
(PHONE RINGS)

451
00:59:05,100 --> 00:59:07,460
- Hello?
SULLIVAN: Sarah.

452
00:59:07,620 --> 00:59:09,290
Mike. Oh, thank God.

453
00:59:09,500 --> 00:59:11,620
I want you to know we're okay.

454
00:59:11,780 --> 00:59:13,300
Where are you?

455
00:59:13,460 --> 00:59:16,220
We're on our way to your place,
if that's all right.

456
00:59:16,540 --> 00:59:19,660
Of course.
I'll be back there in two days.

457
00:59:19,820 --> 00:59:20,860
How's Michael?

458
00:59:21,180 --> 00:59:23,140
He's all right.

459
00:59:25,980 --> 00:59:27,860
How was it?

460
00:59:28,540 --> 00:59:31,220
Oh, Mike...

461
00:59:35,460 --> 00:59:37,450
Hello?

462
00:59:41,500 --> 00:59:43,940
We'll see you soon.

463
01:00:03,740 --> 01:00:06,420
- Hello, operator?
OPERATOR: Yes, sir.

464
01:00:06,580 --> 01:00:09,540
I was just cut off,
could you reconnect me?

465
01:01:14,660 --> 01:01:16,970
You hungry?

466
01:01:17,140 --> 01:01:18,860
No.

467
01:01:19,900 --> 01:01:23,210
Might not be another diner for a while,
so you should eat.

468
01:01:23,380 --> 01:01:24,940
I'm not hungry.

469
01:01:25,100 --> 01:01:27,570
I just wanna read.

470
01:02:54,260 --> 01:02:55,250
(BELL RINGS)

471
01:03:06,540 --> 01:03:09,850
- Slow night, huh?
- You kidding? This is busy.

472
01:03:10,020 --> 01:03:13,010
- What can I get you?
- You got a special?

473
01:03:13,180 --> 01:03:14,770
WAITRESS:
Everything's special.

474
01:03:15,620 --> 01:03:18,980
MAGUIRE: Is that so?
WAITRESS: Everything except the food.

475
01:03:19,540 --> 01:03:21,740
Everything except the food?

476
01:03:22,900 --> 01:03:26,580
- You ought to be on the stage.
WAITRESS: Don't I know it.

477
01:03:26,740 --> 01:03:31,180
MAGUIRE: Give me some honey-dipped
fried chicken and a black coffee.

478
01:03:31,340 --> 01:03:33,380
WAITRESS:
Duck soup.

479
01:03:42,900 --> 01:03:45,100
Don't mind me, sir.

480
01:03:45,820 --> 01:03:49,970
It's a free country.
Used to be, anyhow.

481
01:03:53,220 --> 01:03:54,810
No, thank you, sir.

482
01:04:05,020 --> 01:04:10,490
Is that your profession
or your pleasure?

483
01:04:10,700 --> 01:04:13,460
Both, I guess.

484
01:04:13,980 --> 01:04:17,980
To be paid to do what you love...
Ain't that the dream?

485
01:04:22,420 --> 01:04:24,010
I guess so.

486
01:04:25,020 --> 01:04:26,140
Yourself?

487
01:04:26,460 --> 01:04:28,980
I'm a salesman.
Machine parts.

488
01:04:30,620 --> 01:04:33,180
Machine parts.

489
01:04:33,620 --> 01:04:37,500
- That's wonderful.
- I assure you, it is not.

490
01:04:38,460 --> 01:04:42,340
- So who do you work for?
- Can you keep a secret?

491
01:04:43,940 --> 01:04:45,530
I'm press.

492
01:04:46,180 --> 01:04:48,250
Which paper?

493
01:04:49,180 --> 01:04:52,780
All over.
I'm something of a rarity.

494
01:04:54,180 --> 01:04:55,170
How's that?

495
01:04:55,740 --> 01:04:57,300
I shoot the dead.

496
01:05:01,380 --> 01:05:04,450
Dead bodies, that is.
I don't kill them.

497
01:05:07,700 --> 01:05:09,900
I should hope not.

498
01:05:11,180 --> 01:05:16,810
Always fascinated me,
the look of them, you know?

499
01:05:17,340 --> 01:05:21,700
- You ever seen one?
- Yeah.

500
01:05:21,860 --> 01:05:23,850
Sorry for you.

501
01:05:24,060 --> 01:05:26,180
Terrible thing.

502
01:05:26,580 --> 01:05:29,810
But it sure makes you feel alive,
don't it?

503
01:05:34,980 --> 01:05:37,580
I'll drink to that.

504
01:05:38,340 --> 01:05:40,300
Stuff makes you sweat, huh?

505
01:05:43,420 --> 01:05:44,650
Yeah, piss too.

506
01:05:44,820 --> 01:05:47,970
Excuse me, ma'am,
can you help me out here?

507
01:05:48,220 --> 01:05:50,130
Just through here.

508
01:05:51,540 --> 01:05:54,140
Hey!

509
01:05:54,300 --> 01:05:55,530
Look out, there.

510
01:06:12,620 --> 01:06:15,530
CUSTOMER: Thanks, Ruby.
WAITRESS: Good night.

511
01:06:27,500 --> 01:06:28,700
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

512
01:06:28,860 --> 01:06:29,930
(CAR STARTS)

513
01:06:30,100 --> 01:06:31,930
(DOOR OPENS)

514
01:06:32,100 --> 01:06:33,930
Forgot to leave a tip.

515
01:06:47,060 --> 01:06:48,380
- Get down.
- Why? What's going on?

516
01:06:48,540 --> 01:06:49,900
Get down!

517
01:06:51,180 --> 01:06:53,860
Hey, what do you think you're...?

518
01:07:16,460 --> 01:07:18,500
Get out of the car.

519
01:07:18,860 --> 01:07:22,170
Get out of the car!
When I say get down, you get down.

520
01:07:22,340 --> 01:07:25,300
Don't ask questions. When I say we're
stopping to eat, you stay with me.

521
01:07:25,460 --> 01:07:28,530
You listen to me from now on,
or you start taking care of yourself.

522
01:07:28,780 --> 01:07:32,410
I can take care of myself fine!
You never wanted me along anyway.

523
01:07:32,620 --> 01:07:35,340
- You think it's my fault this happened.
- Stop it.

524
01:07:35,540 --> 01:07:36,900
It was not your fault!

525
01:07:40,380 --> 01:07:43,020
None of this is your fault.

526
01:07:44,380 --> 01:07:48,300
- Just take me to Aunt Sarah's.
- I can't take you there.

527
01:07:48,860 --> 01:07:50,220
Not now.

528
01:07:50,460 --> 01:07:55,410
- Why?
- He knows that's where we're going.

529
01:07:56,540 --> 01:07:58,820
So, what are you gonna do?

530
01:08:01,540 --> 01:08:04,220
Something I can't do alone.

531
01:08:05,620 --> 01:08:10,060
You have to listen to me now, okay?

532
01:08:10,260 --> 01:08:12,900
Or else both of us are dead.

533
01:08:14,060 --> 01:08:16,700
I have to make Capone give up Connor.

534
01:08:16,860 --> 01:08:20,090
There's one thing Chicago loves
more than anything...

535
01:08:20,260 --> 01:08:21,820
...and that's their money.

536
01:08:21,980 --> 01:08:27,140
They've got it in banks all over the
state. We have to find it and take it.

537
01:08:28,900 --> 01:08:32,610
- Are you gonna help me?
- Yes.

538
01:08:34,580 --> 01:08:37,300
Then I have to teach you something.

539
01:08:39,100 --> 01:08:42,620
- You know what the clutch is?
MICHAEL: Sure I know what the clutch is.

540
01:08:42,780 --> 01:08:45,660
SULLIVAN: What is the clutch?
- The clutch, it... It clutches.

541
01:08:45,820 --> 01:08:48,730
Right, it clutches.
Which of those pedals is the clutch?

542
01:08:48,900 --> 01:08:49,890
(ENGINE REVS)

543
01:08:50,060 --> 01:08:51,380
That's the gas.

544
01:08:51,740 --> 01:08:54,260
Gas. I'll show you.

545
01:08:54,420 --> 01:08:55,900
There. Right there, see?

546
01:08:56,060 --> 01:08:58,940
There's the clutch,
and it does the clutching.

547
01:09:05,020 --> 01:09:06,980
Let's go again.

548
01:09:08,540 --> 01:09:11,530
(ENGINE GROANS)

549
01:09:12,060 --> 01:09:14,290
(CAR STARTS)

550
01:09:15,660 --> 01:09:21,660
Release gas, clutch,
shift gear, hit gas...

551
01:09:21,820 --> 01:09:22,810
Shift.

552
01:09:30,500 --> 01:09:33,890
- Can I make one suggestion?
- No.

553
01:09:34,060 --> 01:09:36,260
I'm doing this.

554
01:09:46,820 --> 01:09:49,540
Hey, 45 miles an hour,
that's a little fast.

555
01:09:50,180 --> 01:09:52,300
Look out for the tractor, Mike.

556
01:09:52,540 --> 01:09:55,010
Michael, look out for the tractor.

557
01:09:55,460 --> 01:09:59,060
Watch out for the tractor.
Watch out for the tractor!

558
01:10:01,500 --> 01:10:05,380
MICHAEL: We made it.
- Oh, yeah, yeah, we made it.

559
01:10:06,740 --> 01:10:07,700
(MICHAEL LAUGHS)

560
01:10:17,940 --> 01:10:21,730
No more excuses. I've told you once,
now I'm telling you again...

561
01:10:21,900 --> 01:10:24,700
- I'm looking for a Mr. McDougal.
- Just one moment.

562
01:10:25,100 --> 01:10:27,570
Well, this is a pleasant surprise.

563
01:10:27,740 --> 01:10:30,700
I wasn't expecting another
deposit until the end of the month.

564
01:10:30,900 --> 01:10:34,530
Actually, I'm making a withdrawal.
I want dirty money only.

565
01:10:34,740 --> 01:10:39,340
Everything you're holding for Capone
that's off the books. Open the safe.

566
01:10:41,020 --> 01:10:44,380
You're insane.
You know they'll find out who you are.

567
01:10:44,540 --> 01:10:47,340
The name's Sullivan.
You want me to spell it?

568
01:10:50,140 --> 01:10:51,290
Open the box.

569
01:10:51,740 --> 01:10:54,100
They'll kill you. They're animals.

570
01:10:54,300 --> 01:10:57,690
You don't say. Put it in.

571
01:11:02,420 --> 01:11:03,460
That's for you.

572
01:11:03,780 --> 01:11:06,770
Call it a handling charge.
Tell Chicago I took it.

573
01:11:07,260 --> 01:11:12,180
But if I read about this in the papers,
if I read about the savings of farmers...

574
01:11:12,340 --> 01:11:16,570
...being wiped out by a heartless
bank robber, I won't be happy.

575
01:11:18,060 --> 01:11:20,210
Good afternoon.

576
01:11:20,380 --> 01:11:22,610
You really trust me not to say
anything?

577
01:11:22,780 --> 01:11:24,610
Always trust a bank manager.

578
01:11:39,940 --> 01:11:42,250
There's no rush.

579
01:12:23,460 --> 01:12:25,260
(CAR TIRES SQUEALING)

580
01:12:51,860 --> 01:12:55,090
- Coffee?
SULLIVAN: Thank you.

581
01:13:00,780 --> 01:13:04,250
So, what brings you guys
to the middle of nowhere?

582
01:13:04,420 --> 01:13:06,490
MICHAEL:
We're bank robbers.

583
01:13:07,580 --> 01:13:09,700
We're just passing through.

584
01:13:15,820 --> 01:13:18,700
So when do I get my share
of the money?

585
01:13:21,660 --> 01:13:26,500
Well, how much do you want?

586
01:13:28,700 --> 01:13:30,980
Two hundred dollars.

587
01:13:32,940 --> 01:13:35,500
Okay. Deal.

588
01:13:44,940 --> 01:13:48,540
- Could I have had more?
- You'll never know.

589
01:13:51,580 --> 01:13:53,250
(PHONE RINGS)

590
01:13:56,260 --> 01:13:58,780
(PHONE RINGS)

591
01:14:01,140 --> 01:14:04,050
CONNOR:
Come on, come on.

592
01:14:19,620 --> 01:14:21,770
How much did they take?

593
01:14:21,940 --> 01:14:22,930
How much?

594
01:14:23,100 --> 01:14:24,090
CONNOR:
Get out of my way!

595
01:14:24,260 --> 01:14:27,020
Okay, answer me this:
What are we paying you for?

596
01:14:27,180 --> 01:14:28,900
- Where's my father?
- What's this?

597
01:14:29,140 --> 01:14:30,340
- Why is no one talking to me?
- Hold on.

598
01:14:30,500 --> 01:14:33,140
I feel like a fucking prisoner.

599
01:14:33,580 --> 01:14:37,180
I told you. You are not a prisoner.
You are being protected.

600
01:14:37,340 --> 01:14:40,410
- This is what your father wants.
- I can look after myself.

601
01:14:40,620 --> 01:14:42,980
No, you can't. This is the point.

602
01:14:43,140 --> 01:14:46,740
You're a big baby who doesn't know
his thumb from his dick.

603
01:14:46,900 --> 01:14:47,890
Fuck you.

604
01:14:48,300 --> 01:14:52,850
The only reason you're still alive
is because you're John Rooney's son.

605
01:14:53,020 --> 01:14:56,220
You're being a little
shortsighted here, Frank.

606
01:14:56,380 --> 01:14:59,060
My father is an old man.

607
01:14:59,540 --> 01:15:01,770
I am the future.

608
01:15:02,620 --> 01:15:05,610
So don't you ever talk to me
that way again.

609
01:15:17,980 --> 01:15:22,130
Maguire, do what you have to.
Find them.

610
01:15:22,940 --> 01:15:26,570
BANKER: I'm sorry, Mr. Sullivan,
there is no money.

611
01:15:27,020 --> 01:15:30,700
No... I can get you money, I just...

612
01:15:30,860 --> 01:15:32,220
It won't be Chicago's.

613
01:15:32,380 --> 01:15:35,180
They took it all out two days ago.

614
01:15:39,700 --> 01:15:42,170
- Who authorized it?
- The accountant.

615
01:15:43,100 --> 01:15:44,820
What's his name?

616
01:15:45,060 --> 01:15:47,340
This is Mr. Rance in the bridal suite.

617
01:15:47,500 --> 01:15:51,730
Before you proffer your congratulations,
there's no Mrs. Rance with me...

618
01:15:51,900 --> 01:15:55,130
...and I'm all the better for it.
Listen carefully...

619
01:15:55,300 --> 01:15:57,770
...because I am in no mood.

620
01:15:57,940 --> 01:15:59,980
I'm going to say this only once.

621
01:16:00,140 --> 01:16:03,930
I would like a boiled egg,
and I want it runny.

622
01:16:05,180 --> 01:16:08,780
MICHAEL: Pa, can we sleep in a
motel room tonight instead of the car?

623
01:16:08,940 --> 01:16:11,060
SULLIVAN:
Yeah, that would be nice.

624
01:16:20,460 --> 01:16:23,450
WOMAN: How many more days
you gonna want me, mister?

625
01:16:23,700 --> 01:16:27,380
Can't we close the curtains,
even for a little while?

626
01:16:27,540 --> 01:16:31,010
I can't get no sleep
with all that light.

627
01:16:32,100 --> 01:16:34,700
You see anything,
you hit that horn twice.

628
01:16:34,860 --> 01:16:37,300
Don't get out of the car,
no matter what.

629
01:16:46,980 --> 01:16:48,050
Bye.

630
01:16:53,700 --> 01:16:57,250
- Ready?
- I'm ready.

631
01:17:10,740 --> 01:17:13,970
Yes, sir. Right away, sir.

632
01:17:14,220 --> 01:17:15,660
Runny.

633
01:17:30,100 --> 01:17:31,090
(KNOCKING)

634
01:17:31,260 --> 01:17:32,900
Hm. It's open.

635
01:17:34,220 --> 01:17:38,980
Top marks for speed,
no marks for cookery.

636
01:17:39,140 --> 01:17:42,660
What, may I ask, do you call this?

637
01:17:42,860 --> 01:17:44,060
Put it down.

638
01:17:44,220 --> 01:17:47,420
- Mr. Sullivan.
- Mr. Rance.

639
01:17:47,580 --> 01:17:49,170
How did you find me?

640
01:17:49,340 --> 01:17:54,180
This is the best hotel in the area.
And you are so very particular.

641
01:17:54,380 --> 01:17:56,420
Yes, indeed, Mr. Sullivan.

642
01:17:56,620 --> 01:18:00,090
May I ask you to lower your weapon.

643
01:18:01,020 --> 01:18:03,170
Thank you.
Now, what do you want?

644
01:18:03,340 --> 01:18:04,490
Information.

645
01:18:11,060 --> 01:18:14,020
I can't give you the files.

646
01:18:14,180 --> 01:18:15,850
All right, all right.

647
01:18:16,020 --> 01:18:19,010
They're in the next room.

648
01:18:25,180 --> 01:18:27,940
- In here.
- Bring it in.

649
01:18:35,900 --> 01:18:37,020
I can't see.

650
01:18:40,340 --> 01:18:44,220
What will you accomplish by
interfering with our business?

651
01:18:44,380 --> 01:18:48,530
- This has nothing to do with business.
- It's all business. You fail to grasp that.

652
01:18:48,700 --> 01:18:51,340
And in business, you must
have something to trade.

653
01:18:51,500 --> 01:18:53,810
And you, Mr. Sullivan,
have nothing to trade.

654
01:18:53,980 --> 01:18:57,660
Especially not for anyone
as valuable as Connor Rooney.

655
01:18:57,820 --> 01:18:58,860
I don't understand.

656
01:18:59,020 --> 01:19:00,010
(MACHINE CLICKS)

657
01:19:00,180 --> 01:19:01,980
RANCE:
Opening bell on Wall Street.

658
01:19:04,620 --> 01:19:06,060
Come on, open it.

659
01:19:08,300 --> 01:19:10,340
Which one is it?

660
01:19:29,180 --> 01:19:32,140
No, no, not it.

661
01:19:34,020 --> 01:19:36,540
Tried that one already.

662
01:19:37,660 --> 01:19:39,540
Better start over.

663
01:19:39,860 --> 01:19:41,420
You got one more try.

664
01:19:44,540 --> 01:19:47,100
There it is.

665
01:20:07,540 --> 01:20:09,500
(SCREAMS)

666
01:20:50,540 --> 01:20:52,130
(GUN FIRES)

667
01:20:52,300 --> 01:20:54,180
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

668
01:20:55,340 --> 01:20:56,540
(GUN FIRES)

669
01:20:59,940 --> 01:21:01,580
I'm okay. Watch the road!

670
01:21:08,260 --> 01:21:09,900
(GROANS)

671
01:21:15,740 --> 01:21:16,970
(WHIMPERS)

672
01:21:22,460 --> 01:21:25,450
Pa! Pa, are you okay?

673
01:21:27,140 --> 01:21:28,260
Pa!

674
01:21:28,460 --> 01:21:30,180
Pa!

675
01:21:42,620 --> 01:21:43,900
MICHAEL:
Help!

676
01:21:44,060 --> 01:21:45,100
Help us!

677
01:21:45,940 --> 01:21:47,900
Help!

678
01:21:48,780 --> 01:21:50,260
Help!

679
01:21:50,420 --> 01:21:51,780
Help us!

680
01:22:04,340 --> 01:22:06,700
(SHALLOW BREATHING)

681
01:22:39,660 --> 01:22:42,020
When are you two heading out?

682
01:22:45,220 --> 01:22:47,690
We've stayed long enough.

683
01:22:48,180 --> 01:22:50,700
We don't wanna cause you any trouble.

684
01:22:52,740 --> 01:22:55,130
No trouble so far.

685
01:22:58,660 --> 01:23:01,020
He's a good worker.

686
01:23:02,980 --> 01:23:04,570
You have any kids?

687
01:23:04,740 --> 01:23:06,460
No.

688
01:23:06,780 --> 01:23:09,010
We met too late.

689
01:23:12,260 --> 01:23:14,700
He dotes on you.

690
01:23:19,580 --> 01:23:21,060
You don't see it.

691
01:23:52,100 --> 01:23:54,220
Hello.

692
01:23:55,260 --> 01:23:57,060
I had a bad dream.

693
01:23:58,300 --> 01:23:59,970
You wanna talk about it?

694
01:24:02,580 --> 01:24:05,300
Well, come on in. Take a seat...

695
01:24:05,460 --> 01:24:07,500
...if you want.

696
01:24:20,060 --> 01:24:21,180
Math, huh?

697
01:24:21,340 --> 01:24:23,060
Yeah.

698
01:24:23,220 --> 01:24:25,020
I always hated it.

699
01:24:25,180 --> 01:24:27,140
Me too.

700
01:24:33,020 --> 01:24:34,930
So, what do you like?

701
01:24:35,100 --> 01:24:37,620
Huh?

702
01:24:37,780 --> 01:24:42,380
What subjects do you like...?
Did you like in school?

703
01:24:45,020 --> 01:24:46,980
Bible history, maybe.

704
01:24:48,860 --> 01:24:49,900
Why?

705
01:24:50,980 --> 01:24:52,890
I like the stories.

706
01:24:55,260 --> 01:24:57,620
Peter was good at math.

707
01:25:00,340 --> 01:25:02,380
Was he?

708
01:25:11,260 --> 01:25:13,380
Did you like Peter more than me?

709
01:25:16,420 --> 01:25:18,300
No.

710
01:25:20,220 --> 01:25:22,610
No, Michael.

711
01:25:24,340 --> 01:25:26,860
I loved you both the same.

712
01:25:28,380 --> 01:25:30,530
But you were...

713
01:25:32,140 --> 01:25:35,100
You were different with me.

714
01:25:35,780 --> 01:25:37,740
Was I?

715
01:25:48,380 --> 01:25:50,180
Well...

716
01:25:51,900 --> 01:25:56,420
Maybe it was because Peter was just
such a sweet boy, you know?

717
01:25:59,900 --> 01:26:01,810
And you...

718
01:26:04,860 --> 01:26:07,380
You were more like me.

719
01:26:09,260 --> 01:26:13,860
And I didn't want you to be.

720
01:26:17,420 --> 01:26:20,620
I didn't mean to be...

721
01:26:20,820 --> 01:26:22,780
...different.

722
01:26:27,260 --> 01:26:28,580
Okay.

723
01:26:39,300 --> 01:26:40,700
Good night, Pa.

724
01:26:41,180 --> 01:26:42,900
Good night.

725
01:27:49,020 --> 01:27:53,140
SULLIVAN: Michael, wake up.
Get your things.

726
01:27:53,980 --> 01:27:55,100
We're leaving.

727
01:27:57,420 --> 01:27:58,780
We left you something.

728
01:28:49,020 --> 01:28:51,090
(PRIEST PRAYS IN LATIN)

729
01:29:05,140 --> 01:29:07,100
Hello, John.

730
01:29:15,260 --> 01:29:18,220
You're a smart man, Michael.

731
01:29:20,340 --> 01:29:22,460
I wanna talk.

732
01:29:23,060 --> 01:29:24,810
Here?

733
01:29:25,700 --> 01:29:26,980
Downstairs.

734
01:29:54,020 --> 01:29:56,060
I didn't think I'd see you again.

735
01:29:58,940 --> 01:30:00,090
Read this.

736
01:30:00,740 --> 01:30:03,860
Connor's been stealing from you
for years.

737
01:30:04,220 --> 01:30:09,420
He keeps accounts open under the names
of dead men. Men like the McGoverns.

738
01:30:11,100 --> 01:30:14,620
I stood there and helped him
kill Finn to line his own pockets.

739
01:30:14,780 --> 01:30:18,410
I thought I was working for you,
but I wasn't.

740
01:30:18,580 --> 01:30:20,460
You think I'd give up my son?

741
01:30:20,620 --> 01:30:22,580
He was betraying you.

742
01:30:23,060 --> 01:30:25,180
I know.

743
01:30:25,340 --> 01:30:27,220
Now, listen to me.

744
01:30:27,540 --> 01:30:31,380
I tried to avoid more bloodshed.
You wouldn't accept that...

745
01:30:31,540 --> 01:30:35,580
...so I did what was necessary.
But I've always loved you like a son.

746
01:30:35,740 --> 01:30:40,180
And now I'm telling you,
leave before it's too late.

747
01:30:40,540 --> 01:30:42,290
Think.

748
01:30:43,180 --> 01:30:44,300
Think.

749
01:30:44,460 --> 01:30:48,740
They're protecting him now, but when
you're gone, they won't need him.

750
01:30:48,900 --> 01:30:53,100
- This ends with Connor dead regardless.
- That may be...

751
01:30:53,580 --> 01:30:56,380
...but you are asking me...

752
01:30:56,540 --> 01:30:59,900
...to give you the key to his room
so you can walk in...

753
01:31:00,060 --> 01:31:03,420
...put a gun to his head
and pull the trigger. I can't do that.

754
01:31:03,580 --> 01:31:08,130
- He murdered Annie and Peter.
- There are only murderers in this room.

755
01:31:08,300 --> 01:31:11,530
Michael, open your eyes.

756
01:31:12,220 --> 01:31:15,580
This is the life we chose,
the life we lead.

757
01:31:15,740 --> 01:31:21,930
And there is only one guarantee:
None of us will see heaven.

758
01:31:22,140 --> 01:31:24,260
Michael could.

759
01:31:24,420 --> 01:31:30,290
Then do everything that you can
to see that that happens.

760
01:31:30,460 --> 01:31:33,900
Leave.
I'm begging you.

761
01:31:34,660 --> 01:31:36,730
It's the only way.

762
01:31:39,460 --> 01:31:40,940
And if I go?

763
01:31:42,260 --> 01:31:44,140
Then...

764
01:31:44,300 --> 01:31:46,980
...I will mourn...

765
01:31:48,060 --> 01:31:49,860
...the son I lost.

766
01:31:57,180 --> 01:31:58,620
(DOOR CLOSES)

767
01:32:46,300 --> 01:32:47,740
What are you gonna do?

768
01:32:48,860 --> 01:32:52,490
Just one last thing,
and then it's done.

769
01:32:58,140 --> 01:33:00,260
Go back to bed, Michael.

770
01:36:10,700 --> 01:36:12,900
I'm glad it's you.

771
01:36:26,140 --> 01:36:27,660
(GUN FIRES)

772
01:37:25,460 --> 01:37:27,050
I understand.

773
01:37:27,220 --> 01:37:32,580
But then Al wants your assurance
that after that, it's over.

774
01:37:36,100 --> 01:37:40,970
The Lexington Hotel, room 1432.

775
01:38:03,580 --> 01:38:05,020
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

776
01:41:04,060 --> 01:41:05,890
Is that the house?

777
01:41:06,700 --> 01:41:08,180
SULLIVAN:
That's it.

778
01:41:08,340 --> 01:41:09,330
(DOG BARKS)

779
01:41:09,500 --> 01:41:10,820
MICHAEL:
Hey.

780
01:41:10,980 --> 01:41:13,130
I knew there was a dog.

781
01:41:55,060 --> 01:42:00,140
SULLIVAN: Sarah? It's me, Mike.
We're here.

782
01:42:36,060 --> 01:42:37,810
(GUN FIRES)

783
01:43:28,420 --> 01:43:29,980
Smile.

784
01:43:36,700 --> 01:43:37,690
(GUN COCKS)

785
01:43:55,700 --> 01:43:57,260
Give me the gun.

786
01:43:57,780 --> 01:43:58,820
Michael.

787
01:44:02,420 --> 01:44:03,540
Michael...

788
01:44:04,420 --> 01:44:06,410
...don't you do this.

789
01:44:07,420 --> 01:44:09,090
Give me the gun, Michael.

790
01:44:12,900 --> 01:44:14,300
Come on.

791
01:44:15,020 --> 01:44:17,010
Give me the gun.

792
01:44:19,740 --> 01:44:21,620
(GUN FIRES)

793
01:44:31,100 --> 01:44:32,820
I couldn't do it.

794
01:44:35,220 --> 01:44:37,020
I know.

795
01:44:44,180 --> 01:44:47,330
- Pa.
- I'm sorry.

796
01:44:47,500 --> 01:44:50,300
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

797
01:44:55,220 --> 01:44:56,860
I'm sorry.

798
01:45:02,620 --> 01:45:03,900
Pa.

799
01:45:05,180 --> 01:45:06,900
Pa!

800
01:45:07,580 --> 01:45:09,140
Pa!

801
01:45:18,100 --> 01:45:19,540
Pa.

802
01:45:20,940 --> 01:45:24,380
Pa! Pa!

803
01:46:11,460 --> 01:46:15,540
MICHAEL: I saw then
that my father's only fear...

804
01:46:15,780 --> 01:46:18,980
...was that his son
would follow the same road.

805
01:46:21,100 --> 01:46:24,220
And that was the last time
I ever held a gun.

806
01:46:53,140 --> 01:46:56,580
People always thought
I grew up on a farm.

807
01:46:56,740 --> 01:47:02,340
And I guess, in a way, I did.

808
01:47:04,900 --> 01:47:07,580
But I lived a lifetime before that...

809
01:47:07,740 --> 01:47:10,460
...in those six weeks on the road...

810
01:47:10,620 --> 01:47:13,340
...in the winter of 1931.

811
01:47:22,700 --> 01:47:26,620
When people ask me if Michael Sullivan
was a good man...

812
01:47:27,180 --> 01:47:30,460
...or if there was just no good
in him at all...

813
01:47:31,260 --> 01:47:33,650
...I always give the same answer.

814
01:47:36,100 --> 01:47:38,410
I just tell them:

815
01:47:39,780 --> 01:47:42,140
"He was my father."

